---
import SchemaLayout from '../../../layouts/SchemaLayout.astro';
import drugsData from '../../../../data/drugs.json';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const slug = 'renal';
const displayName = 'Renal';

const drugs = (drugsData as any[]).filter(
  (d: any) => (d.organ_systems || []).includes(slug)
);
const drugCount = drugs.length;
---
<SchemaLayout title="Renal Pharmacology" schema="organ-systems" description="Drugs classified under the Renal organ system">

  <div class="mb-6">
    <div class="breadcrumbs text-sm mb-4">
      <ul>
        <li><a href={`${base}schemas/01-organ-systems/`} class="link">Organ Systems</a></li>
        <li>Renal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-base-content mb-2">Renal</h1>
    <p class="text-base-content/70 text-lg">{drugCount} drug{drugCount !== 1 ? 's' : ''} in this system</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose max-w-none mb-10">
    <p>The kidney is both a pharmacological target and the primary route of elimination for approximately one-third of clinically used drugs. Renal pharmacology encompasses three functional domains: diuresis and fluid homeostasis, protection of glomerular and tubular function in the setting of hypertension and diabetes, and management of the metabolic consequences of renal failure. The nephron's segmental anatomy defines drug targets: carbonic anhydrase in the proximal tubule, the Na-K-2Cl cotransporter (NKCC2) in the thick ascending limb, the Na-Cl cotransporter (NCC) in the distal convoluted tubule, and aldosterone-sensitive sodium channels (ENaC) in the collecting duct. Vasopressin V2 receptors govern free water reabsorption via aquaporin-2 insertion. Disease states managed here include edematous states (heart failure, cirrhosis, nephrotic syndrome), hypertension, hyponatremia, hyperkalemia, CKD-mineral bone disorder, and polyuria syndromes.</p>
    <p>Loop diuretics -- furosemide, bumetanide, and torsemide -- block NKCC2 with high efficacy regardless of GFR, making them the diuretics of choice in acute decompensated heart failure and severe fluid overload. Their ceiling effect requires dose titration rather than simple escalation; IV formulations reach peak diuresis within 30 to 60 minutes and nurses must monitor urine output hourly in acute settings while assessing for hypokalemia, hypomagnesemia, and ototoxicity with high doses. Thiazides act on NCC in the distal tubule and retain efficacy only above GFR 30 mL/min; their combination with loop diuretics produces synergistic diuresis in diuretic resistance. Potassium-sparing diuretics -- spironolactone, eplerenone (competitive aldosterone receptor antagonists) and triamterene, amiloride (ENaC blockers) -- are invaluable in heart failure and hyperaldosteronism but carry serious hyperkalemia risk when combined with ACE inhibitors, ARBs, or in patients with CKD. Newer mineralocorticoid receptor antagonists such as finerenone demonstrate cardiorenal protection in diabetic CKD independent of diuretic effect.</p>
    <p>Renal protection in CKD centers on blocking the RAAS to reduce intraglomerular hypertension and proteinuria, and on SGLT2 inhibition in the proximal tubule. SGLT2 inhibitors (empagliflozin, dapagliflozin, canagliflozin) reduce glomerular hyperfiltration by tubuloglomerular feedback activation and independently slow CKD progression. Nursing must monitor serum creatinine and potassium within one to two weeks of initiating or up-titrating any RAAS-blocking agent; an acute creatinine rise of up to 30 percent is acceptable and expected with ACE inhibitors and ARBs reflecting normalization of efferent arteriolar tone, but rises exceeding 30 percent warrant investigation for renal artery stenosis. Phosphate binders (sevelamer, calcium acetate, lanthanum carbonate) and calcimimetics (cinacalcet) manage CKD-mineral bone disorder; cinacalcet activates the calcium-sensing receptor on parathyroid chief cells and must be administered with food to reduce nausea, with calcium monitored before each dose to prevent hypocalcemia.</p>
  </div>

  {drugs.length === 0 && (
    <div class="alert alert-info mb-6">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-current shrink-0 w-6 h-6"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
      <span>No drugs are currently classified under this organ system. Check back as more drug data is added.</span>
    </div>
  )}

  {drugs.length > 0 && (
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      {drugs.map((drug: any) => (
        <div class={`card card-compact bg-base-100 shadow border border-base-200 ${drug.ismp_high_alert ? 'border-l-4 border-l-error' : ''}`}>
          <div class="card-body">
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-1 mb-1">
              <h2 class="card-title text-base font-semibold capitalize mr-auto">
                <a href={`${base}drugs/${drug.id}/`} class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">
                  {drug.generic_name}
                </a>
              </h2>
              {drug.prototype_for && (
                <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">PROTOTYPE</span>
              )}
              {drug.ismp_high_alert && (
                <span class="badge badge-error badge-sm shrink-0">HIGH ALERT</span>
              )}
              {drug.black_box_warnings && drug.black_box_warnings.length > 0 && (
                <span class="badge badge-warning badge-sm shrink-0">BBW</span>
              )}
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60 mb-1">
              <span class="font-medium">{drug.drug_class}</span>
              {drug.subclass && <span> &mdash; {drug.subclass}</span>}
            </p>
            {drug.mechanism_summary && (
              <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70 line-clamp-3">{drug.mechanism_summary}</p>
            )}
            <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-2">
              <a href={`${base}drugs/${drug.id}/`} class="btn btn-xs btn-outline btn-primary">Profile</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  )}

</SchemaLayout>
